comment:
Y'all are missing the point. It's a hilarious throwback to the 80's - they did that well.
I used to love Rapinoe, certainly as a player and I agreed with most of her message.
When she turned her message into an agenda, she put it before the sport and the fans that pay her salary, I started slowly losing respect for her. She simultaneously lost all humility, wearing ridiculous ego stroking outfits and going on talk shows - now I just find her annoying.
However, she did forever change the women's game for the better, and she helped us win a couple world cups. For that, as a man, I'm grateful and proud of her contribution.
